I am running a REST (oldskool) action:

 {{<server>/api/rest/executeBuild.action?buildKey=<plan key>&auth=<token>}}

The following error is returned:

{code}
<errors> 
    <error>You need to provide the buildKey.</error> 
</errors>
{code}

I was trying to do something like this in my listener:
{code:java}
final ChainCompletedEvent chainCompletedEvent = (ChainCompletedEvent) event;

// update dependencies only if chain has completed successfully
if (chainCompletedEvent.getBuildContext().getBuildResult().getBuildState() == BuildState.SUCCESS)
{code}
but getBuildState() returns BuildState.UNKNOWN every time.

Example Line
{code}Can't clobber writable file /test/blah/blah.txt{code}
Bamboo should recognise this and fail the build.

DeletionService uses:

FileUtils.deleteDir(SystemDirectory.getBuildWorkingDirectory(plan.getKey()));
           FileUtils.deleteDir(SystemDirectory.getBuildDownloadDataDirectory(plan.getKey()));
           FileUtils.deleteDir(SystemDirectory.getBuildDataDirectory(plan.getKey()));


this won't work with concurrent builds (since these directories are 'namespaced' with the agent id).
Apart from scheduling these deletions, we have to interate over all agentIds dirs available in the
parents of these directories and schedule additional deletions there as well.

{code}
2010-09-17 15:56:18,063 INFO [BAM::Events:pool-1-thread-15] [PostBuildCompletedEventListener] Running build post actions 'The Project Of Doom - P4 Chain - p4subplan1'
2010-09-17 15:56:18,070 INFO [BAM::Events:pool-1-thread-15] [PostBuildCompletedEventListener] Build post process aborted. Build CHAINPROJ-P4-P4SUBPLAN1 has been deleted.
{code}

Its still using the old interfaces.
